# Project Context

Monorepo containing 4 UK niche accountancy websites. All live, deployed on Vercel, sharing a common architecture.

## Sites

| Site | Domain | niche_id | Blog URL pattern | Posts |
|------|--------|----------|-----------------|-------|
| Property Tax Partners | propertytaxpartners.co.uk | property | /blog/{category}/{slug} | 85 |
| Dental Finance Partners | dentalfinancepartners.co.uk | dentists | /blog/{category}/{slug} | 55 |
| Medical Accountants UK | medicalaccountantsuk.co.uk | medical | /blog/{slug} (flat) | 46 |
| Accounts for Lawyers | accountsforlawyers.co.uk | solicitors | /blog/{category}/{slug} | 50 |

Medical uses flat blog URLs. The other 3 use /blog/{category-slug}/{post-slug}.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind 4
- App Router (src/app/)
- Supabase (leads, blog topics)
- Vercel deployment
- Python (Anthropic API) for blog content generation
- GSC/GA4 integration via agents/

## Folder Structure

```
Accounting/
├── Property/              # Each site follows this pattern:
│   ├── niche.config.json  #   Site config (domain, brand, categories, SEO)
│   ├── web/               #   Next.js app
│   │   ├── src/app/       #     Pages (App Router)
│   │   ├── src/lib/       #     blog.ts, schema.ts, local-business-schema.ts
│   │   ├── src/config/    #     site.ts, niche-loader.ts
│   │   ├── src/components/#     UI components
│   │   └── content/blog/  #     Markdown blog posts with YAML front matter
│   └── pipeline/          #   Python blog generation scripts
├── Dentists/              # Same structure as Property
├── Medical/               # Same structure (flat blog URLs, no category in path)
├── Solicitors/            # Same structure as Property
├── shared/
│   └── web-core/          #   Shared TS: schema.ts, blog.ts, components
├── agents/                # Python agent system (GSC, blog gen, analytics)
├── scripts/               # Utility scripts (Batch/Canonicals/Database/Generation/Import/Migration/Monitoring/Testing)
├── supabase/              # DB migrations + applied SQL
├── Admin/                 # Audit doc + Topics (keyword CSVs) + archive
